HEADWORD: Enchoric
<hw>En*chor"ic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ domestic, native; <?/
in + <?/ place, country.]</ety> <def>Belonging to, or used in, a
country; native; domestic; popular; common; -- said especially of the
written characters employed by the common people of ancient Egypt, in
distinction from the hieroglyphics. See <er>Demotic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

